OL,3,CQueen Elizabeth II's official
OL,4,Cbiographer named
OL,6,FWilliam Shawcross's official biography
OL,7,Fof Elizabeth, the Queen Mother
OL,8,Frevealed she believed Edward VIII was
OL,9,F"bemused with love" at the time of his
OL,10,Fabdication and how she suffered from
OL,11,Fbowel cancer in her 60s but was
OL,12,Fsuccessfully treated.
OL,14,FMs Keay said on her appointment: "It
OL,15,Fis a profound honour to have been
OL,16,Fasked to write the official biography
OL,17,Fof Queen Elizabeth II.
OL,19,F"She was our longest-reigning monarch
OL,20,Fand an extraordinary woman, whose life
OL,21,Fspanned a century of great change."
